        "subtask": false,
        "avatarId": 21140
      },
      "components": [],
      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2013-07-26T00:13:23.853+0000",
      "description": "Today we allocate resource (memory and cpu) and node manager starts the container with requested resource [I am assuming they are using cgroups]. But there is definitely a possibility of users requesting more than what they actually may need during the execution of their container/job-task. If we add a way for users/AM to know the actual usage of the requested/completed container then they may optimize it for next run..\n\nThis will be helpful for AM to optimize cpu/memory resource requests by querying NM/RM to know avg/max cpu/memory usage of the container or may be containers belonging to application.",
      "priority": {
